**3. How The Website Works**
Simple flow:

```text
User uploads CV PDF
        ↓
JavaScript reads PDF using PDF.js
        ↓
User uploads full_dataset.json
        ↓
JavaScript reads the JSON
        ↓
System compares CV skills with job skills
        ↓
Website shows recommended jobs, match score, gap skills and summary
```

Because GitHub Pages is static, it cannot run Python/Flask. So the live site works using JavaScript inside the browser.

